HEADWORD: Nippitate
<hw>Nip"pi*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. 1st
<er>Nip</er>.]</ety> <def>Peculiarly strong and good; -- said of ale or
liquor.</def> <mark>[Old Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T will make a cup of wine taste <qex>nippitate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nippitato</ent>⟦br⟧
